originalText.text: I placed an order today through Uber eats, but I only received one of my meals. I don't know what kind of scam some of these Uber eats driver are running, but they'll try contacting you before they arrive at the drop off location and if you don't respond, they'll cancel your order. My driver tried that today. Not the first driver to try it, though, so I'm on to them. He arrived with two of my meals missing, but when I called the restaurant, they said my order was complete. Anyways, one of the restaurant workers drove to my location to drop off the missing orders. That was really nice of her. I honestly appreciate it cause that was supposed to be my dinner for tomorrow. Thank u.
